From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 06:51:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] provenance: opt-in --vars; record rhs, dereferences, and
 execution context
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Variable tracing is now OPT-IN: `sarun run --vars` (exports
SARUN_TRACE_VARS=1 into the box; both recorders early-return without
it) — a yocto-scale build pays nothing by default.

Each makevar row additionally records HOW the assignment looked and
what fed it: the UNEXPANDED rhs text (kati stmt.orig_rhs / brush's
assignment AST, capped 1KB) and the variable names it dereferences
(text scan; make function heads excluded, $(call NAME,…)/$(value
NAME) count their first argument) — plus its execution context: the
recipe edge's primary output and the enclosing pipeline uid (a
builtin sub-make parses on the invoking recipe's thread, so its
assignments anchor to the spawning edge). review.makevars resolves
those anchors to build_edges/brushprov row ids in the same query and
grows an any-mode (OR name/value) for single-term searches. The kati
hook also reports the ASSIGNMENT site (+= points at the append, not
the original :=).

test_make_rs.py case 24 covers rhs/refs, edge anchoring of shell and
sub-make assignments, and that an untraced box records zero rows.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B97aMMA3rHQW7gsyBB2Cpa
---
 src-rs/eval.rs     | 2 +-
 src-rs/fileutil.rs | 9 ++++++---
 2 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src-rs/eval.rs b/src-rs/eval.rs
index 05aeb70..c6ec536 100644
--- a/src-rs/eval.rs
+++ b/src-rs/eval.rs
@@ -760,7 +760,7 @@ impl Evaluator {
             let val = g.string().unwrap_or(std::borrow::Cow::Borrowed(b""));
             crate::fileutil::report_var_assign(
                 &lhs.as_bytes(), &loc, &val,
-                self.working_dir.as_os_str().as_bytes());
+                self.working_dir.as_os_str().as_bytes(), &stmt.orig_rhs);
         }
         Ok(())
     }
diff --git a/src-rs/fileutil.rs b/src-rs/fileutil.rs
index 99cfd63..395832e 100644
--- a/src-rs/fileutil.rs
+++ b/src-rs/fileutil.rs
@@ -394,8 +394,9 @@ pub fn clear_glob_cache() {
 // them into the box's capture database so wrong-value hunts are a query, not
 // a rerun with trace flags. Same Arc-clone-then-release pattern as the other
 // hooks (the callback may allocate / send frames).
+/// (name, loc, expanded value, make working dir, UNEXPANDED rhs text)
 pub type VarAssignHook =
-    Arc<dyn Fn(&[u8], &str, &[u8], &[u8]) + Send + Sync + 'static>;
+    Arc<dyn Fn(&[u8], &str, &[u8], &[u8], &[u8]) + Send + Sync + 'static>;
 
 static VAR_ASSIGN_HOOK: parking_lot::Mutex<Option<VarAssignHook>> =
     parking_lot::Mutex::new(None);
@@ -404,9 +405,11 @@ pub fn install_var_assign_hook(f: VarAssignHook) {
     *VAR_ASSIGN_HOOK.lock() = Some(f);
 }
 
-pub fn report_var_assign(name: &[u8], loc: &str, value: &[u8], make_dir: &[u8]) {
+pub fn report_var_assign(
+    name: &[u8], loc: &str, value: &[u8], make_dir: &[u8], rhs: &[u8],
+) {
     let h = VAR_ASSIGN_HOOK.lock().clone();
     if let Some(h) = h {
-        h(name, loc, value, make_dir);
+        h(name, loc, value, make_dir, rhs);
     }
 }
